Package: dataVisEasy
Type: Package
Title: datavisEasy: Data visualizations Using Annotations Made Easy
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Alison Moss
Maintainer: Alison Moss <alisonmoss3@gmail.com>
Description: A user friendly package to aid in visualization of transcriptomic (or proteomic or any other type of expression) datasets. By setting up annotations to the data, the user can seamlessly run a variety of analysis and data visualziations that integrate annotations in an intuitive way.Functions in this package are linked to a list object that stores parameters and annotations common to the dataset being analyzed and is utilized across most functions within the dataVisEasy pacakge. 
Depends: 
    pheatmap,
    ggplot2,
    R (>= 2.10)
Imports: 
    pcaMethods,
    scales,
    tibble,
    cluster,
    ggbeeswarm,
    gtools,
    dplyr,
    reshape2,
    RColorBrewer,
    magrittr
License: What license is it under?
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
Suggests: 
